%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2F2020%2F03%2F24%2Fworld%2Fasia%2Findia-coronavirus-lockdown.html%5C%22%20data-saferedirecturl%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.google.com%2Furl%3Fq%3Dhttps%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2F2020%2F03%2F24%2Fworld%2Fasia%2Findia-coronavirus-lockdown.html%26amp%3Bsource%3Dgmail%26amp%3Bust%3D1705382793712000%26amp%3Busg%3DAOvVaw3swha33p8UCXGWCN7ecg7l%5C%22%3Eannounced%3C%2Fa%3E%20the%20first%20COVID-19%20lockdown%20on%20the%20evening%20of%20March%2024%2C%202020%2C%20as%20the%20number%20of%20active%20cases%20in%20the%20country%20rose%20to%20500.%20The%20first%20phase%20of%20it%20would%20last%20for%2021%20days%2C%20effectively%20preventing%20the%20country%E2%80%99s%201.3%20billion-strong%20population%20from%20stepping%20out%20of%20their%20homes%20and%20also%20cutting%20down%20on%20the%20rate%20of%20spread%20of%20the%20virus.%20However%2C%20the%20sudden%20announcement%20of%20the%20lockdown%20also%20led%20to%20a%20panic-stricken%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theguardian.com%2Fworld%2F2020%2Fmar%2F30%2Findia-wracked-by-greatest-exodus-since-partition-due-to-coronavirus%5C%22%20data-saferedirecturl%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.google.com%2Furl%3Fq%3Dhttps%3A%2F%2Fwww.theguardian.com%2Fworld%2F2020%2Fmar%2F30%2Findia-wracked-by-greatest-exodus-since-partition-due-to-coronavirus%26amp%3Bsource%3Dgmail%26amp%3Bust%3D1705382793712000%26amp%3Busg%3DAOvVaw3QAuZK50rsZSwYpcbGd-92%5C%22%3Eexodus%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0of%20millions%20of%20migrant%20workers%2C%20many%20of%20whom%20worked%20in%20daily-wage%20jobs%2C%20from%20big%20cities%20and%20towns%20to%20their%20native%20villages%2C%20resulting%20in%20several%20deaths.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20title%20of%20the%20poem%20refers%20to%20the%20first%20phase%20of%2021%20days%20%E2%80%94%20the%20lockdown%20would%20be%20extended%20several%20times%20and%20imposed%20with%20different%20levels%20of%20severity%2C%20depending%20on%20the%20state%20of%20the%20pandemic.%20But%20it%20is%20also%20a%20reference%20to%20the%202002%20zombie-apocalypse%20horror%20film%20%3Cem%3E28%20Days%20Later%3C%2Fem%3E.%20Directed%20by%20Danny%20Boyle%2C%20it%20stars%20Cillian%20Murphy%2C%20who%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2Fgoldenglobes%2Fstatus%2F1744188296090263783%5C%22%20data-saferedirecturl%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.google.com%2Furl%3Fq%3Dhttps%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2Fgoldenglobes%2Fstatus%2F1744188296090263783%26amp%3Bsource%3Dgmail%26amp%3Bust%3D1705382793712000%26amp%3Busg%3DAOvVaw1Z0dvSWFM7KHXgC2vaFj6G%5C%22%3Erecently%20won%3C%2Fa%3E%20a%20Golden%20Globe%20for%20his%20performance%20in%20the%20biopic%20%3Cem%3EOppenheimer%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20as%20a%20survivor.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMhatre%E2%80%99s%20poem%20is%20also%20about%20surviving%20the%20pandemic%2C%20reuniting%20with%20loved%20ones%20at%20the%20end%20of%20a%20long%20period%20of%20uncertainty%20and%20anxiety%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESeveral%20planes%20take%20off%20in%20a%20unified%20choir%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWhere%20to%3F%E2%80%9D%20I%20ask%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CTo%20each%20other.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETwenty-one%20days%20dissolve%20in%20an%20embrace.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHere%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EI%20am%20still%20waiting%20for%20you%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%E2%80%99s%20Day%20One%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3Eat%20the%20airport%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20last%20stanza%20of%20the%20poem%20is%20a%20reaffirmation%20of%20the%20renewal%20of%20the%20planet%20and%20everyone%20on%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESince%202019%2C%20when%20the%20pandemic%20entered%20our%20lives%2C%20poets%20around%20the%20world%20have%20tried%20to%20respond%20to%20it%20%E2%80%94%20not%20always%20with%20great%20success.%20An%20anthology%2C%20%3Cem%3ETogether%20in%20a%20Sudden%20Strangeness%3A%20America%E2%80%99s%20Poets%20Respond%20to%20the%20Pandemic%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20edited%20by%20Alice%20Quinn%2C%20former%20poetry%20editor%20of%3Cem%3E%20The%20New%20Yorker%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20published%20in%20late%202020%2C%20was%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2F2020%2F12%2F14%2Fbooks%2Freview-together-in-sudden-strangeness-pandemic-poetry-alice-quinn.html%5C%22%20data-saferedirecturl%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.google.com%2Furl%3Fq%3Dhttps%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2F2020%2F12%2F14%2Fbooks%2Freview-together-in-sudden-strangeness-pandemic-poetry-alice-quinn.html%26amp%3Bsource%3Dgmail%26amp%3Bust%3D1705382793712000%26amp%3Busg%3DAOvVaw3d9HFrUZN3LZU4j5GIiWVx%5C%22%3Edescribed%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0by%20the%20%3Cem%3ENew%20York%20Times%3C%2Fem%3E%20as%20faltering%20%E2%80%9Con%20every%20front%E2%80%9D.%20Despite%20a%20few%20misses%2C%20however%2C%20poetry%20did%20prove%20to%20be%20therapeutic%20%E2%80%94%20with%20even%20mental%20health%20professionals%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2F2021%2F04%2F12%2Fwell%2Fmind%2Fnational-poetry-month-coronavirus.html%5C%22%20data-saferedirecturl%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.google.com%2Furl%3Fq%3Dhttps%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2F2021%2F04%2F12%2Fwell%2Fmind%2Fnational-poetry-month-coronavirus.html%26amp%3Bsource%3Dgmail%26amp%3Bust%3D1705382793712000%26amp%3Busg%3DAOvVaw1hnGcmJOR9q7iEr8lA8GOj%5C%22%3Eadvising%20their%20patients%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0and%20clients%20to%20read%20more%20verse.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20India%2C%20too%2C%20several%20poets%20have%20responded%20to%20the%20pandemic%2C%20trying%20to%20make%20sense%20of%20their%20own%20survival%20or%20loss.%20One%20of%20the%20first%20books%20to%20respond%20to%20the%20pandemic%20in%20India%20was%20%3Cem%3ESinging%20in%20the%20Dark%3A%20A%20Global%20Anthology%20of%20Poetry%20Under%20Lockdown%3C%2Fem%3E%20(2020)%3Cem%3E%2C%C2%A0%3C%2Fem%3Eedited%20by%20K.%20Satchidanandan%20and%20Nishi%20Chawla.%20(I%20had%20also%20contributed%20a%20few%20poems%20to%20it.)%20Nikita%20Parik%E2%80%99s%20powerful%20collection%2C%20%3Cem%3E%E2%80%98%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fbooks%2Fcrows-nikita-parik-poetry-review%5C%22%20data-saferedirecturl%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.google.com%2Furl%3Fq%3Dhttps%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fbooks%2Fcrows-nikita-parik-poetry-review%26amp%3Bsource%3Dgmail%26amp%3Bust%3D1705382793712000%26amp%3Busg%3DAOvVaw0SI2nkFIGGCIJTXMPPlk0a%5C%22%3EMy%20City%20is%20Murder%20of%20Crows%20%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fem%3E(2022)%2C%20addresses%20the%20cocktails%20of%20emotions%20sparked%20by%20surviving%20the%20deadly%20second%20wave%20of%20the%20pandemic.%20Vinita%20Agarwal%E2%80%99s%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Natural%20Language%20of%20Grief%3C%2Fem%3E%20(2022)%20also%20bears%20witness%20to%20the%20ravages%20of%20the%20disease.%20Mhatre%E2%80%99s%20book%20is%20a%20suitable%20addition%20to%20this%20rich%20and%20growing%20body%20of%20work.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20titular%20poem%20of%20the%20book%20refers%20to%20the%20sirens%20of%20ambulances%20taking%20Mhatre%E2%80%99s%20mother%20%E2%80%94%20Aai%2C%20in%20Marathi%20%E2%80%94%20to%20the%20hospital%20after%20she%20is%20detected%20with%20stage-three%20cancer%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20a%20rain-kissed%20day%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3Esirens%20from%20ambulances%20wring%20at%20full%20volume%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3Esending%20a%20shockwave%20through%20this%20somnolence%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3Ethe%20city%20has%20been%20suddenly%20diagnosed%20with%20Stage%203C%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20image%20of%20the%20murder%20is%20fused%20with%20the%20image%20of%20the%20city%2C%20and%20the%20breathless%20lines%20of%20the%20poem%20follow%20each%20other%2C%20without%20as%20much%20as%20a%20comma%2C%20like%20machine%20gun%20fire.%20Medical%20terms%20make%20too%20frequent%20appearances.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3Enow%2C%20water%20levels%20are%20rising%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3Eher%20stomach%20bloats%20with%20a%20spell%20of%20monsoon%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3Eand%20there%E2%80%99s%20no%20omental%20biopsy%20in%20sight%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3Eno%20cytology%20report%20collected%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnyone%20who%20has%20ever%20served%20as%20a%20caregiver%20will%20provide%20testimony%20to%20the%20sheer%20anxiety%20of%20waiting%20for%20hours%20in%20cold%20waiting%20rooms%20of%20hospitals%20and%20nursing%20homes%2C%20for%20medical%20reports%2C%20treatment%2C%20for%20tests.%20This%20poem%20examines%20the%20contours%20of%20bereavement%2C%20which%20sometimes%20begins%20with%20a%20diagnosis%2C%20long%20before%20the%20actual%20event%20of%20death.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20introduction%20to%20this%20book%2C%20dedicated%20to%20Mhatre%E2%80%99s%20mother%2C%20he%20writes%3A%20%E2%80%9CShe%20was%20diagnosed%20with%20Stage%203C%20Ovarian%20Cancer.%20I%20could%20feel%20the%20voice%20of%20sirens%2C%20the%20constant%20beat%20of%20cardiograms%20filling%20up%20my%20veins%20as%20my%20father%20broke%20the%20news%20to%20me.%20From%20then%2C%20the%20sound%20of%20sirens%20became%20second%20nature.%20Synchronised%20to%20my%20heartbeat.%E2%80%9D%20But%20the%20sound%20of%20sirens%20is%20not%20only%20the%20bugle%20of%20fear%20and%20loss%3B%20it%20can%20also%20be%20a%20sound%20of%20hope.%20As%20Mhatre%20reports%2C%20his%2093-year-old%20grandmother%E2%80%99s%20recovery%20from%20Covid-19%20became%20a%20story%20of%20hope%3A%20%E2%80%9CThe%20sound%20of%20sirens%20was%20celebrating%20our%20survival.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDeath%20has%20served%20as%20an%20inspiration%20to%20poets%20since%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.britannica.com%2Ftopic%2FGilgamesh%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EGilgamesh%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0was%20written%20some%204%2C000%20years%20ago.%20But%20not%20every%20expression%20of%20death%20and%20loss%20%E2%80%94%20and%20survival%20%E2%80%94%20can%20be%20epic.%20Even%20in%20its%20most%20quotidian%20expressions%2C%20it%20can%20provide%20relief%2C%20hope%2C%20and%20catharsis.%20Mhatre%E2%80%99s%20book%20does%20succeed%20in%20doing%20this.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EUttaran%20Das%20Gupta%20is%20a%20New%20Delhi-based%20writer%20and%20journalist.%20He%20teaches%20journalism%20at%20O.P.%20Jindal%20Global%20University%2C%20Sonipat%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1705324817000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2F30153449%2FACF098D3-6123-4B67-A2E4-DCA712B4.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fbooks%2Fof-poems-pandemics-and-death%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Sanket%20Mhatre%E2%80%99s%20collection%20of%20poems%20reflects%20on%20a%20city%20in%20the%20grip%20of%20Covid-19%2C%20but%20also%20celebrates%20surviving%20it.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A2%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fbooks%2Fof-poems-pandemics-and-death%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22%26quot%3BNo%20Food%2C%20Restless%20Children%26quot%3B%3A%20Fliers%20Claim%20Harrowing%20Air%20India%20Flight%20Delay%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EThe%20passenger%20of%20an%20Air%20India%20plane%20who%20remained%20stuck%20inside%20the%20aircraft%20for%20six%20hours%20has%20pointed%20to%20several%20factors%20that%20sparked%20anger%20among%20people%2C%20after%20several%20airlines%20cancelled%20hundreds%20of%20fights%20due%20to%20low%20visibility%20in%20Delhi%20yesterday.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnother%20passenger%2C%20seen%20in%20a%20viral%20video%20of%20him%20slapping%20an%20IndiGo%20pilot%2C%20has%20been%20arrested%2C%20the%20police%20said.%20The%20passenger%2C%20Sahil%20Kataria%2C%20was%20released%20on%20bail%20later.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERifka%20Verma%2C%20the%20Air%20India%20passenger%2C%20told%20NDTV%20today%20their%20patience%20ran%20thin%20due%20to%20a%20combination%20of%20factors%20-%20children%20getting%20restless%2C%20not%20getting%20food%2C%20and%20air-conditioning%20not%20working.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20flight%20was%20to%20take-off%20at%209%20am.%20It%20was%20obvious%20seeing%20the%20weather%20condition%20it%20would%20be%20delayed.%20But%20they%20kept%20giving%20conflicting%20information.%20After%202%20pm%2C%20when%20the%20aircraft%20was%20ready%2C%20they%20said%20they%20don't%20have%20a%20crew%20as%20that%20crew%20has%20been%20put%20on%20another%20flight%2C%26quot%3B%20Ms%20Verma%20told%20NDTV.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20was%20absolute%20chaos.%20After%20they%20got%20a%20crew%20it%20was%205.30%20pm.%20We%20boarded%20around%208%20pm.%20There%20was%20no%20pilot.%20I%20don't%20think%20the%20ground%20staff%20or%20the%20crew%20is%20to%20blame.%20It's%20the%20management%2C%20or%20rather%20mismanagement...%20There%20was%20no%20food%2C%20only%20some%20packets%20of%20chips%20in%2017%20hours%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThey%20are%20not%20valuing%20their%20customers%2C%20and%20not%20keeping%20them%20informed%2C%26quot%3B%20Ms%20Verma%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESmooth%20coordination%20in%20Delhi%20airport%20broke%20down%20yesterday%20after%20hundreds%20of%20passengers%20of%20delayed%20flights%20demanded%20answers%20from%20the%20airlines.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20stressful%20day%20also%20saw%20the%20passenger%20of%20an%20IndiGo%20flight%20attacking%20a%20pilot%20inside%20the%20plane%20while%20it%20was%20on%20the%20tarmac.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAir%20India%20in%20a%20statement%20today%20said%20it%20regrets%20the%20disruption%20to%20operations%20arising%20from%20the%20last%20few%20days'%20dense%20fog%20in%20north%20India%2C%20including%20at%20%26quot%3Bour%20main%20Delhi%20hub%2C%20which%20resulted%20in%20some%20diversions%20and%20desynchronisation%20of%20aircraft%20and%20crew%20rotations.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20are%20working%20hard%20to%20restore%20schedules%2C%20and%20sincerely%20regret%20the%20inconvenience%20caused%20to%20our%20passengers%2C%26quot%3B%20Air%20India%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ECivil%20Aviation%20Minister%20Jyotiraditya%20Scindia%20today%20said%20they%20have%20taken%20steps%20to%20avoid%20similar%20circumstances%20in%20the%20future.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BYesterday%2C%20Delhi%20witnessed%20unprecedented%20fog%20wherein%20visibility%20fluctuated%20for%20several%20hours%2C%20and%20at%20times%2C%20dropped%20to%20zero%20between%205%20am%20and%209%20am%2C%26quot%3B%20Mr%20Scindia%20posted%20on%20X.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20authorities%2C%20therefore%2C%20were%20compelled%20to%20enforce%20a%20shut-down%20of%20operations%20for%20some%20time%20even%20on%20CAT%20III%20runways%20(CAT%20III%20runways%20cannot%20handle%20zero-visibility%20operations).%20The%20decision%20was%20taken%20keeping%20passenger%20safety%20in%20mind%2C%20which%20remains%20the%20foremost%20priority%20for%20all%20in%20the%20aviation%20ecosystem%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Union%20Minister%20suggested%20operationalising%20the%20CAT%20III-enabled%20fourth%20runway.%20The%20regulator%20Directorate%20General%20of%20Civil%20Aviation%20(DGCA)%20will%20release%20a%20standard%20operating%20procedure%20(SOP)%20aimed%20at%20enhancing%20communication%20and%20passenger%20facilitation%20for%20airlines.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThis%20measure%20aims%20to%20minimise%20passenger%20discomfort%20caused%20by%20flight%20cancellations%20and%20delays%20attributed%20to%20adverse%20weather%20conditions%2C%26quot%3B%20Mr%20Scindia%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1705324740000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-01%2Fei93tab_air-india-flight-horror-650_625x300_15_January_24.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fair-india-flight-horror-17-hour-wait-for-delhi-mumbai-passengers-4867405%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20passenger%20of%20an%20Air%20India%20plane%20who%20remained%20stuck%20inside%20the%20aircraft%20for%20six%20hours%20has%20pointed%20to%20several%20factors%20that%20sparked%20anger%20among%20people%2C%20after%20several%20airlines%20cancelled%20hundreds%20of%20fights%20due%20to%20low%20visibility%20in%20Delhi%20yesterday.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fair-india-flight-horror-17-hour-wait-for-delhi-mumbai-passengers-4867405%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-ndtv-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fair-india-flight-horror-17-hour-wait-for-delhi-mumbai-passengers-4867405%2Famp%2F1%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fair-india-flight-horror-17-hour-wait-for-delhi-mumbai-passengers-4867405%2Famp%2F1%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Two%20high-value%20Russian%20planes%20'shot%20down'%2C%20Ukraine%20claims%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1705324680000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fe3.365dm.com%2F24%2F01%2F768x432%2Fskynews-a-50-ukraine-russia-plane_6422378.jpg%3F20240115135431%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Ftwo-high-value-russian-planes-shot-down-ukraine-claims-13048952%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Two%20high-value%20Russian%20aircraft%20have%20been%20shot%20down%2C%20Ukraine%20has%20claimed%2C%20in%20what%20would%20be%20a%20major%20blow%20to%20its%20air%20force.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A12%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Ftwo-high-value-russian-planes-shot-down-ukraine-claims-13048952%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews-sky-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Famp%2Ftwo-high-value-russian-planes-shot-down-ukraine-claims-13048952%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Famp%2Ftwo-high-value-russian-planes-shot-down-ukraine-claims-13048952%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Phone%20Charging%20To%20Be%20Redundant%3F%20China%20Firm%20Makes%20Battery%20With%2050-Year%20Life%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EA%20start-up%20in%20China%20has%20created%20a%20new%20battery%20that%20it%20claims%20can%20generate%20electricity%20for%2050%20years%20without%20the%20need%20for%20charging%20or%20maintenance.%20A%20report%20in%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.independent.co.uk%2Ftech%2Fnuclear-battery-betavolt-atomic-china-b2476979.html%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EThe%20Independent%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20it's%20a%20nuclear%20battery%20developed%20by%20Beijing-based%20Betavolt.%20And%20don't%20imagine%20a%20massive%20size%20after%20reading%20the%20word%20%26quot%3Bnuclear%26quot%3B.%20Betavolt%20has%20managed%20to%20squeeze%2063%20isotopes%20into%20that%20module%20that's%20smaller%20than%20a%20coin%2C%20the%20outlet%20further%20said%20in%20its%20report.%20The%20company%20said%20it%20is%20the%20first%20battery%20in%20the%20world%20to%20realise%20the%20miniaturisation%20of%20atomic%20energy.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20next-generation%20battery%20is%20already%20being%20tested%20and%20will%20be%20mass%20produced%20for%20commercial%20applications%20like%20phones%20and%20drones.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BBetavolt%20atomic%20energy%20batteries%20can%20meet%20the%20needs%20of%20long-lasting%20power%20supply%20in%20multiple%20scenarios%2C%20such%20as%20aerospace%2C%20AI%20equipment%2C%20medical%20equipment%2C%20microprocessors%2C%20advanced%20sensors%2C%20small%20drones%20and%20micro-robots%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20company%20said%20in%20a%20press%20release.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThis%20new%20energy%20innovation%20will%20help%20China%20gain%20a%20leading%20edge%20in%20the%20new%20round%20of%20the%20AI%20technological%20revolution%2C%26quot%3B%20it%20further%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch3%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20dimensions%20of%20the%20battery%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20measures%2015%20x%2015%20x%205%20millimetres%20and%20is%20made%20of%20wafer-thin%20layers%20of%20nuclear%20isotopes%20and%20diamond%20semiconductors%2C%20as%20per%20Futurism.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20nuclear%20battery%20currently%20generates%20100%20microwatts%20of%20power%20at%203%20volts.%20However%2C%20the%20goal%20is%20to%20reach%20a%201-watt%20power%20output%20by%202025.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBetavolt%20said%20the%20radiation%20poses%20no%20danger%20to%20the%20human%20body%2C%20making%20it%20usable%20in%20medical%20devices%20such%20as%20pacemakers.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch3%3E%3Cstrong%3EHow%20does%20the%20battery%20work%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20technology%20used%20in%20the%20battery%20taps%20into%20the%20energy%20from%20decaying%20isotopes%2C%20a%20concept%20that%20was%20first%20explored%20in%20the%2020th%20century.%20It%20then%20converts%20this%20energy%20into%20electricity.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EChina%20has%20been%20working%20towards%20miniaturising%20nuclear%20batteries%20under%20its%2014th%20Five-Year%20Plan%20from%202021-2025.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20battery%20has%20a%20layered%20design%2C%20which%20will%20prevent%20it%20from%20catching%20fire%20or%20exploding%20due%20to%20sudden%20force.%20Betavolt%20also%20claimed%20that%20the%20battery%20is%20capable%20of%20working%20in%20temperatures%20ranging%20from%20-60%20degrees%20Celsius%20to%20120%20degrees%20Celsius.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAtomic%20energy%20batteries%20are%20environmentally%20friendly.%20After%20the%20decay%20period%2C%20the%2063%20isotopes%20turn%20into%20a%20stable%20isotope%20of%20copper%2C%20which%20is%20non-radioactive%20and%20does%20not%20pose%20any%20threat%20or%20pollution%20to%20the%20environment.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20mass%20production%20of%20the%20battery%20is%20expected%20to%20begin%20after%20the%20company%20completes%20testing%20and%20receives%20all%20the%20necessary%20clearances.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1705324620000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-01%2Fc0pv51io_betavolt-nuclear-battery_625x300_15_January_24.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fscience%2Fchina-firm-claims-its-coin-sized-battery-could-generate-50-year-electricity-without-charging-4867655%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Betavolt%20said%20the%20radiation%20of%20the%20nuclear%20battery%20poses%20no%20danger%20to%20the%20human%20body%2C%20making%20it%20usable%20in%20medical%20devices%20such%20as%20pacemakers.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A17%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fscience%2Fchina-firm-claims-its-coin-sized-battery-could-generate-50-year-electricity-without-charging-4867655%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-ndtv-com.cdn.ampproject.org