%80%99t%20want%20to%20be%20king%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20is%20said%20to%20have%20shouted%20to%20his%20nanny%20as%20a%20child.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFrederik%E2%80%99s%20wild%20days%20as%20a%20rebellious%20%E2%80%9Cparty%20prince%E2%80%9D%20have%20long%20since%20passed.%20He%20and%20his%20Australian%20wife%2C%20Mary%2C%20have%20produced%20heirs%20to%20the%20throne%2C%20guaranteeing%20the%20continuation%20of%20the%20oldest%20royal%20dynasty%20in%20Europe.%20His%20subjects%20seem%20to%20approve%2C%20with%20polls%20finding%20that%2080%25%20of%20Danes%20are%20satisfied%20with%20their%20ruler.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.dw.com%2Fen%2Fvictoria-crown-princess%2Ft-38325059%5C%22%3ESwedish%20Crown%20Princess%20Victori%3C%2Fa%3Ea%20and%20Norwegian%20Prince%20Haakon%20are%20next%20up%20for%20their%20respective%20thrones.%20Victoria%20is%20in%20line%20to%20take%20over%20from%20her%20father%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.dw.com%2Fen%2Fcarl-xvi-gustaf%2Ft-38293219%5C%22%3ECarl%20XVI%20Gustaf%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20who%20has%20been%20on%20the%20throne%20for%20over%2050%20years.%20Haakon%20would%20replace%20his%2086-year-old%20father%2C%20King%20Harald%20V%2C%20who%20now%20rarely%20appears%20in%20public%20because%20of%20his%20ill%20health.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ERoyal%20%E2%80%98soap%20opera%E2%80%99%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20Europe%2C%20kings%20and%20queens%20have%20generally%20ceremonial%20roles%2C%20with%20scant%20political%20power.%20This%20applies%20to%20the%20princely%20houses%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.dw.com%2Fen%2Fluxembourg%2Ft-40075872%5C%22%3ELuxembourg%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20Liechtenstein%2C%20along%20with%20the%20dwarf%20state%20of%20Monaco%2C%20where%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.dw.com%2Fen%2Falbert-ii%2Ft-38292497%5C%22%3EPrince%20Albert%20II%3C%2Fa%3E%20has%20a%20relatively%20strong%20position.%20Another%20dwarf%20state%2C%20Andorra%2C%20tucked%20between%20the%20high%20valley%20of%20France%20and%20Spain%2C%20always%20has%20two%20co-princes%20who%20act%20as%20heads%20of%20state.%20One%20prince%20is%20the%20Spanish%20bishop%20of%20Urgell%3B%20the%20other%20is%20the%20president%20of%20France.%20This%20means%20that%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.dw.com%2Fen%2Femmanuel-macron%2Ft-38774225%5C%22%3EEmmanuel%20Macron%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20not%20only%20currently%20the%20president%20of%20the%20Republic%20of%20France%2C%20but%20also%20a%20prince%20in%20the%20parliamentary%20democracy%20of%20Andorra.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20only%20elective%20monarchy%20in%20Europe%20where%20the%20throne%20is%20not%20hereditary%20is%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.dw.com%2Fen%2Fvatican%2Ft-39325063%5C%22%3E%20the%20Vatican%3C%2Fa%3E.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.dw.com%2Fen%2Fpope-francis%2Ft-17449437%5C%22%3EPope%20Francis%3C%2Fa%3E%20not%20only%20heads%20the%20Catholic%20Church%2C%20but%20is%20also%20the%20absolute%20ruler%20of%20the%20world%E2%80%99s%20smallest%20state%3A%20Vatican%20City.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CI%20think%20most%20citizens%20of%20states%20with%20a%20monarchical%20order%20actually%20enjoy%20their%20monarchy%2C%E2%80%9D%20University%20of%20Potsdam%20historian%20and%20royals%20expert%20Monika%20Wienfort%20said.%20There%20have%20been%20no%20serious%20efforts%20to%20abolish%20this%20form%20of%20government%20in%20the%20seven%20sovereign%20royal%20houses%20and%20five%20principalities%20in%20Europe.%20Resignations%20and%20successions%20have%20been%20seamless%20apart%20from%20minor%20protests%20by%20republican-minded%20groups%2C%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERoyalty%20has%20persisted%20throughout%20Europe%20wherever%20there%20were%20no%20revolutionary%20upheavals%2C%20such%20as%20those%20in%20France%2C%20Italy%2C%20Austria%20or%20Germany.%20As%20almost%20all%20royal%20houses%20are%20somehow%20related%20to%20each%20other%2C%20and%20chiefly%20to%20German%20nobility%2C%20there%20would%20always%20be%20the%20possibility%20of%20moving%20in%20with%20relatives%20in%20a%20pinch%2C%20Wienfort%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERoyal%20houses%20thrive%20on%20tradition%2C%20gossip%2C%20scandals%20and%20the%20public%20display%20of%20a%20happy%20family%20life%2C%20increasingly%20free%20of%20pomp%20and%20glitter.%20%E2%80%9CI%20think%20we%E2%80%99re%20a%20soap%20opera%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20United%20Kingdom%E2%80%99s%20then%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.dw.com%2Fen%2Fking-charles-iii%2Ft-36992023%5C%22%3EPrince%20Charles%3C%2Fa%3E%20said%20about%20his%20family%20in%202008.%20His%20father%2C%20Philip%2C%20once%20also%20described%20the%20Windsors%20as%20a%20company%20tasked%20with%20producing%20beautiful%20images%20to%20aspire%20to%20in%20return%20for%20taxpayers%E2%80%99%20money.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E43%20monarchies%20globally%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20monarchy%20model%20rules%20in%2022%25%20of%20the%20countries%20in%20the%20world%2C%20or%2043%20of%20the%20194%20formally%20recognized%20states.%20In%20addition%20to%20Europe%2C%20monarchies%20can%20be%20found%20in%20the%20Caribbean%2C%20Africa%2C%20the%20Middle%20East%20and%20Asia.%20Many%20date%20back%20to%20the%20British%20Empire%2C%20and%20the%20British%20king%20is%20still%20the%20head%20of%20state%20in%2014%20countries%20outside%20Europe%20%E2%80%94%20including%20Canada%20and%20Australia.%20Japan%20is%20the%20only%20empire%20in%20the%20world%2C%20though%20the%20Tenno%20has%20purely%20ceremonial%20duties%20in%20the%20country%E2%80%99s%20democracy.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20six%20countries%2C%20the%20monarch%2C%20sheikh%20or%20emir%20is%20the%20absolute%20ruler%20without%20parliamentary%20or%20judicial%20control%3A%20Brunei%2C%20Oman%2C%20Qatar%2C%20Saudi%20Arabia%2C%20Eswatini%20(formerly%20Swaziland)%20and%20the%20aforementioned%20Vatican%20City.%20In%20some%20countries%2C%20such%20as%20Jordan%20or%20Morocco%2C%20the%20king%20has%20political%20power%20determined%20by%20the%20constitution.%20In%20Asia%2C%20Malaysia%20has%20the%20only%20major%20elective%20monarchy%2C%20currently%20held%20by%20Sultan%20Abdullah%20Sultan%20Ahmad%20Shah%2C%20determined%20by%20the%20sultans%20of%20the%20country%E2%80%99s%20nine%20provinces.%20In%20the%20United%20Arab%20Emirates%2C%20the%20office%20of%20head%20of%20state%20also%20rotates%20among%20the%20emirs%2C%20the%20authoritarian%20leaders%20of%20their%20respective%20principalities.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThere%20is%20no%20tabloid%20press%20in%20the%20Middle%20East%20to%20publicly%20report%20royal%20dramas%2C%20but%20gossip%20about%20monarchs%20is%20big%20business%20in%20Europe.%20The%20market%20leader%20is%20still%20the%20British%20royal%20family%2C%20even%20without%20the%20queen%2C%20who%20reigned%20for%2070%20years%20and%20died%20in%202022.%20Public%20interest%20in%20the%20dysfunctional%20family%20dramas%20surrounding%20King%20Charles%3B%20his%20sons%2C%20William%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.dw.com%2Fen%2Fharry%2Ft-38325177%5C%22%3EHarry%3C%2Fa%3E%3B%20and%20wife%2C%20Camilla%2C%20remains%20steady.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20fascination%20stems%20from%20the%20spectacular%20in%20the%20everyday%2C%E2%80%9D%20Wienfort%20said.%20The%20royals%20do%20completely%20normal%20things%20such%20as%20marry%2C%20raise%20children%20and%20die.%20But%20their%20biographies%20are%20representative%20and%20luxurious%2C%20or%20even%20pompous%2C%20she%20said.%20People%20want%20to%20look%20at%20carriages%2C%20uniforms%2C%20dresses%20and%20castles%2C%20even%20if%20they%20don%E2%80%99t%20feel%20any%20particular%20awe.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBeing%20a%20monarch%20is%20also%20fairy%20tale-level%20lucrative.%20The%20richest%20king%20in%20the%20world%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.dw.com%2Fen%2Fthailand%2Ft-63342744%5C%22%3EThailand%3C%2Fa%3E%E2%80%98s%20Rama%20X%2C%20is%20worth%20%2430%20billion%20to%20%2443%20billion%20(%E2%82%AC27.3-%E2%82%AC39%20billion)%2C%20according%20to%20estimates%20by%20US%20business%20magazines.%20Europe%E2%80%99s%20richest%20prince%20is%20H