of%20crisis%2C%20the%20relief%20NGO%20Oxfam%20said%20in%20its%20latest%20report%2C%20arguing%20that%20the%20world%20today%20faces%20a%20fundamental%20choice%20between%20ushering%20in%20an%20age%20of%20%E2%80%9Cbillionaire%20supremacy%E2%80%9D%20and%20repurposing%20the%20economy%20to%20serve%20the%20interests%20of%20the%20many.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20opening%20statistic%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Foxfamilibrary.openrepository.com%2Fbitstream%2Fhandle%2F10546%2F621583%2Fbp-inequality-inc-150124-en.pdf%5C%22%3Ethis%20report%2C%20titled%20%E2%80%98Inequality%20Inc.%E2%80%99%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20is%20that%20since%202020%2C%20five%20billion%20people%20%E2%80%93%2060%25%20of%20the%20global%20population%20%E2%80%93%20grew%20poorer%20but%20the%20world%E2%80%99s%20five%20richest%20men%20doubled%20their%20wealth.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOxfam%20also%20estimated%20that%20if%20the%20wealth%20of%20the%20five%20richest%20billionaires%20continued%20to%20rise%20at%20the%20same%20rate%20as%20it%20has%20over%20the%20past%20half-decade%2C%20the%20world%20will%20see%20its%20first%20trillionaire%20within%20ten%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CHowever%2C%20we%20will%20not%20eliminate%20poverty%20for%20230%20years%2C%E2%80%9D%20it%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20just%20three%20years%2C%20the%20world%20has%20seen%20a%20global%20pandemic%2C%20war%20and%20a%20cost-of-living%20crisis%2C%20Oxfam%20said%2C%20adding%20that%20these%20did%20not%20just%20widen%20the%20gulf%20between%20the%20rich%20and%20poor%2C%20but%20%E2%80%9Cbetween%20an%20oligarchic%20few%20and%20the%20vast%20majority%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20NGO%20said%20that%20increasing%20monopolisation%20had%20%E2%80%9Csupercharged%E2%80%9D%20global%20corporate%20power%2C%20which%20it%20described%20as%20pursuing%20higher%20returns%20to%20shareholders%20above%20all%20other%20goals.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20went%20on%20to%20identify%20four%20ways%20in%20which%20corporate%20power%20fuelled%20inequality%3A%20forcing%20wages%20down%20and%20directing%20profits%20to%20the%20super-rich%3B%20avoiding%20taxes%3B%20privatising%20public%20services%3B%20and%20driving%20(and%20spinning%20the%20truth%20about)%20climate%20change.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOxfam%20highlighted%20how%20the%20latter%20two%20ways%20could%20drive%20inequalities%20along%20gender%2C%20race%2C%20caste%20or%20class.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cdiv%3E%3Ciframe%20allowfullscreen%3D%5C%22allowfullscreen%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fembed%2Fz0deAkw42DM%3Fsi%3DBxSK9qtgPSUwFZu3%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22560%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22YouTube%20video%20player%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22315%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20case%20of%20privatisation%20in%20India%2C%20it%20said%20that%20Dalits%20faced%20higher%20costs%20and%20overt%20discrimination%20in%20the%20private%20healthcare%20and%20education%20sectors.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOxfam%20also%20said%20that%20while%20the%20World%20Bank%E2%80%99s%20private%20sector%20arm%20had%20invested%20over%20half%20a%20billion%20dollars%20in%20India%E2%80%99s%20private%20health%20sector%2C%20it%20has%20%E2%80%9Cnot%20published%20a%20single%20evaluation%20of%20its%20health%20projects%20in%20India%20since%20these%20started%20over%2025%20years%20ago.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CSupporting%20private%20healthcare%20in%20a%20context%20where%2037%25%20of%20Indians%20experience%20catastrophic%20health%20expenditures%20in%20private%20hospitals%20appears%20to%20run%20counter%20to%20the%20World%20Bank%20Group%E2%80%99s%20focus%20on%20poverty%20reduction%2C%E2%80%9D%20it%20had%20said%20in%20an%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.oxfam.org%2Fen%2Fresearch%2Ffirst-do-no-harm-examining-impact-ifcs-support-private-healthcare-india%5C%22%3Eearlier%20study%20published%20in%20June%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20also%20said%20that%20this%20arm%20of%20the%20World%20Bank%20had%20invested%20in%20high-end%20urban%20hospitals%20in%20India%2C%20adding%20that%20several%20such%20hospitals%20had%20consistently%20failed%20to%20provide%20free%20care%20to%20the%20poor%20despite%20being%20required%20to%20do%20so%20in%20return%20for%20receiving%20subsidised%20government%20land.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitical-economy%2Ffour-things-india-must-do-to-achieve-economic-equality-social-justice%5C%22%3EFour%20Things%20India%20Must%20Do%20to%20Achieve%20Economic%20Equality%2C%20Social%20Justice%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENear%20the%20end%20of%20its%20report%2C%20Oxfam%20called%20on%20governments%20to%20reduce%20wealth%20inequality%20by%20creating%20a%20dynamic%20and%20effective%20state%2C%20reining%20in%20corporate%20power%20and%20freeing%20businesses%20from%20%E2%80%9Cshareholder%20greed%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThis%20is%20not%20radical.%20What%E2%80%99s%20radical%20is%20letting%20such%20extremes%20persist%2C%E2%80%9D%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fx.com%2FRebecca_Riddell%2Fstatus%2F1746685875910508812%3Fs%3D20%5C%22%3Esaid%20Rebecca%20Riddell%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20one%20of%20the%20report%E2%80%99s%20authors%2C%20on%20X%20(formerly%20Twitter).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAmitabh%20Behar%2C%20Oxfam%20International%E2%80%99s%20interim%20executive%20director%2C%20also%20emphasised%20the%20need%20to%20rein%20in%20%E2%80%9Crunaway%20corporate%20power%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWe%20have%20the%20evidence.%20We%20know%20the%20history.%20Public%20power%20can%20rein%20in%20runaway%20corporate%20power%20and%20inequality%20%E2%80%93%20shaping%20the%20market%20to%20be%20fairer%20and%20free%20from%20billionaire%20control%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20was%20quoted%20as%20saying%20by%20an%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.oxfam.org%2Fen%2Fpress-releases%2Fwealth-five-richest-men-doubles-2020-five-billion-people-made-poorer-decade-division%5C%22%3EOxfam%20press%20release%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20continued%3A%20%E2%80%9CGovernments%20must%20intervene%20to%20break%