202023%20performers%2C%20may%20suffer%20if%20gains%20for%20Eurosceptic%20parties%20are%20seen%20as%20weakening%20the%20commitment%20to%20European%20integration.%20The%20EU%20raising%20joint%20debt%20to%20back%20the%20post-pandemic%20recovery%20has%20helped%20reduce%20the%20perceived%20riskiness%20of%20Italian%20debt.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWith%20the%20EU%20parliament%20heavily%20involved%20in%20legislation%20and%20electing%20the%20next%20head%20of%20the%20bloc's%20executive%2C%20watch%20the%20readout%20on%20further%20support%20for%20Ukraine%20and%20climate%20policy.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ERUSSIA%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDate%3A%20March%2017%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EVladimir%20Putin%2C%20who%20was%20handed%20the%20presidency%20by%20Boris%20Yeltsin%20on%20the%20last%20day%20of%201999%2C%20is%20certain%20to%20win%20another%20six%20years%20in%20power.%20Polling%20shows%20Putin%20enjoys%20approval%20ratings%20of%20above%2080%20per%20cent%20in%20Russia.%20Opposition%20politicians%20say%20the%20election%20is%20a%20carefully%20stage-managed%20imitation%20of%20democracy.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EKey%20market%20risk%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20campaign%2C%20Putin%20may%20reveal%20more%20of%20his%20thinking%20about%20the%20war%20in%20Ukraine.%20Putin%20has%20warned%20the%20West%20any%20attempts%20to%20meddle%20in%20the%20election%20will%20be%20considered%20an%20act%20of%20aggression.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWestern%20governments%20such%20as%20the%20United%20States%20and%20Japan%20are%20considering%20seizing%20frozen%20Russian%20assets%20such%20as%20cash%20and%20government%20bonds%20held%20by%20its%20central%20bank%20overseas.%20Russia%20has%20said%20it%20will%20retaliate%20if%20that%20happens.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERussia's%20economy%20has%20been%20boosted%20by%20massive%20increases%20in%20defence%20spending%20on%20the%20war%2C%20though%20stubborn%20inflation%20fanned%20by%20a%20sharp%20rouble%20depreciation%20has%20forced%20interest%20rates%20higher.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ETURKEY%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDate%3A%20March%2031%20(local%20election)%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20return%20to%20orthodox%20economics%20following%20President%20Tayyip%20Erdogan's%20May%20re-election%20has%20started%20to%20lure%20back%20international%20investors.%20JPMorgan%20reckons%202024%20could%20be%20a%20record%20year%20for%20international%20bond%20issuance.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EKey%20market%20risk%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20weak%20lira%20and%20inflation%20topping%2060%20per%20cent%20is%20leading%20to%20worries%20on%20Erdogan%20pulling%20back%20on%20the%20orthodox%20pivot.%20Neither%20widely%20respected%20Finance%20Minister%20Mehmet%20Simsek%20or%20plucked-from-Wall-Street%20Central%20Bank%20Governor%20Hafize%20Gaye%20Erkan%20are%20expected%20to%20bend%20easily.%20Erdogan%20has%20a%20history%20of%20turning%20on%20a%20dime%20and%20has%20fired%20four%20central%20bank%20chiefs%20in%20as%20many%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EINDIA%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDate%3A%20April-May%2C%20to%20be%20confirmed%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPrime%20Minister%20Narendra%20Modi%20is%20expected%20to%20win%20a%20third%20term%20as%20Prime%20Minister%20leading%20the%20BJP%20in%20national%20elections.%20Investors%20moving%20cash%20out%20of%20China%20have%20turned%20to%20India.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EKey%20market%20risk%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPersistent%20inflation%20could%20hurt%20the%20BJP.%20PM%20Modi%20would%20need%20to%20form%20a%20coalition%20if%20it%20does%20not%20win%20an%20outright%20majority.%20Key%20commodity%20exporter%20India%20has%20roiled%20markets%20by%20restricting%20rice%2C%20wheat%20and%20sugar%20exports.%20A%20shift%20back%20to%20fiscal%20populism%20risks%20pushing%20up%20India's%20fiscal%20deficit%2C%20which%20would%20need%20funding%20from%20potentially%20record%20high%20domestic%20market%20borrowing.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EMEXICO%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDate%3A%20June%202%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPresidential%20election%20will%20involve%20a%20full%20Congress%20reshuffle%20and%20nine%20state%20elections.%20Polls%20give%20incumbent%20National%20Regeneration%20Movement%20(Morena)%20party%20and%20its%20candidate%2C%20ex-Mexico%20City%20mayor%20Claudia%20Sheinbaum%2C%20a%20wide%20double-digit%20lead.%20A%20more%20balanced%20Congress%20preventing%20constitutional%20changes%20from%20populist%20Morena%20is%20anticipated.%20But%20given%20the%20success%20of%20current%20President%20Andres%20Manuel%20Lopez%20Obrador's%20spending%20drives%2C%20Sheinbaum%20is%20expected%20to%20follow%20suit.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EKey%20market%20risk%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHeftier%20spending%20could%20pull%20down%20Mexico's%20peso%20and%20hurt%20government%20bonds.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ESOUTH%20AFRICA%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDate%3A%20May-August%202024%2C%20to%20be%20confirmed%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20ruling%20African%20National%20Congress%20risks%20losing%20its%20parliamentary%20majority%20in%20elections%20for%20the%20first%20time%20since%20Nelson%20Mandela%20led%20it%20to%20power%20in%201994.%20Economic%20turmoil%2C%20power%20cuts%2C%20austerity%2C%20and%20graft%20allegations%20have%20alienated%20voters.%20The%20ANC%20may%20need%20to%20partner%20with%20the%20Democratic%20Alliance%20or%20the%20Marxist%20Economic%20Freedom.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EKey%20market%20risk%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPre-election%2C%20the%20government%20could%20ease%20austerity%2C%20pushing%20up%20debt.%20If%20the%20ANC%20allies%20with%20a%20leftist%20party%2C%20social%20spending%20could%20rise.%20Worries%20about%20a%20weak%20currency%20and%20public%20finances%20could%20slow%20down%20rate%20cuts.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EUNITED%20STATES%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDate%3A%20November%205%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDonald%20Trump%20is%20predicted%20to%20win%20the%20Republican%20nomination%20in%20upcoming%20primaries%2C%20setting%20the%20stage%20for%20a%20tight%20battle%20with%20Democrat%20incumbent%20Joe%20Biden%20-%20a%20rerun%20of%20the%202020%20election%20that%20ended%20with%20a%20pro-Trump%20mob%20storming%20Congress%20in%20an%20attempt%20to%20block%20certification%20of%20Biden's%20victory.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETrump%20faces%20criminal%20trials%20in%20four%20jurisdictions%20and%20an%20array%20of%20other%20legal%20cases%2C%20while%20he%20still%20claims%20falsely%20that%20the%202020%20election%20was%20stolen.%20Biden%20calls%20his%20opponent%20a%20threat%20to%20democracy%20who%20would%20seek%20vengeance%20on%20his%20many%20foes%20if%20he%20regains%20power.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMarket%20risks%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMarkets%20shrugged%20off%20the%20violence%20that%20followed%20the%20election%20four%20years%20ago.%20But%20given%20the%20heated%20rhetoric%20on%20both%20sides%20this%20time%20around%2C%20a%20Trump-Biden%20rematch%20could%20still%20worry%20investors%20over%20the%20risk%20of%20social%20unrest.%20A%20bitter%20election%20could%20affect%20consumer%20sentiment%20as%20the%20world's%20biggest%20economy%20seeks%20to%20avert%20a%20recession%20from%20the%20lagged%20effects%20of%20aggressive%20interest%20rate%20rises.%20The%20dollar%20could%20swing%20on%20election%20probabilities.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EStocks%20could%20be%20hurt%20by%20caution%20over%20U.S.-China%20tensions%20if%20the%20parties%20harness%20the%20popularity%20of%20trade%20barriers%2C%20with%20analysts%20saying%20higher%20tariffs%20would%20fuel%20inflation%2C%20force%20up%20the%20dollar%20and%20hurt%20the%20yuan%2C%20euro%20and%20Mexican%20peso.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESpending%20cut%20pledges%20by%20either%20party%20could%20upend%20a%20complex%20but%20popular%20U.S.%20bonds%20trade%20that%20wagers%20government%20borrowing%20will%20increase.%20And%20watch%20oil%3A%20Trump%20favours%20more%20U.S.%20drilling%2C%20which%20Biden%20has%20reined%20in.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EBRITAIN%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDate%3A%20Due%20by%20January%202025%2C%20expected%20by%20end-2024%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20opposition%20Labour%20party