h-china-is-not-an-option-taiwan-ruling-party-vp-candidate-says-2023-11-23%2F%5C%22%3Efailed%20negotiation%20attempts%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20November%2023.%20With%20Taiwan%E2%80%99s%20traditional%20media%20heavily%20aligned%20with%20either%20the%20Kuomintang%20or%20the%20government%2C%20the%20Taiwan%20People%E2%80%99s%20Party%20faced%20an%20uphill%20battle%20for%20airtime.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EInstead%20of%20ceding%20the%20stage%2C%20they%20went%20digital.%20They%20launched%20their%20own%20YouTube%20channel%2C%20and%20their%20supporters%20spearheaded%20online%20and%20offline%20campaigns%20and%20created%20alternative%20news%20channels.%20This%20counteroffensive%20transformed%20the%20fight%20into%20a%20three-pronged%20clash.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20battle%20became%20more%20than%20just%20a%20contest%20between%20the%20establishment%20and%20the%20anti-establishment.%20It%20morphed%20into%20a%20clash%20between%20traditional%20media%20and%20the%20burgeoning%20power%20of%20social%20media.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Taiwan%20People%E2%80%99s%20Party%E2%80%99s%20digital%20insurgency%20challenged%20the%20long-held%20dominance%20of%20traditional%20media%20and%20carved%20out%20a%20space%20for%20their%20voices%20to%20be%20heard.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20the%20outcome%20of%20the%20election%20may%20be%20set%2C%20the%20digital%20battleground%20shows%20a%20new%20force%20has%20emerged%20in%20Taiwan%E2%80%99s%20political%20landscape.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20future%20of%20the%20cross-strait%20relations%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20the%20international%20front%2C%20continuity%20seems%20to%20be%20the%20watchword.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20established%20relationship%20with%20the%20US%2C%20nurtured%20by%20President%20Tsai%20Ing-wen%2C%20is%20likely%20to%20continue%20under%20the%20guidance%20of%20Vice%20President%20Bi%20khim%20Hsiao.%20Her%20esteemed%20record%20as%20former%20ambassador%20to%20the%20US%20inspires%20confidence%20in%20maintaining%20strong%20ties.%3C%2Fp%3E%5